## ═══════════════════════════════════════════
## SECTION 11: SECURITY IMPLEMENTATION
## ═══════════════════════════════════════════

```
Layer 1: HTTPS
  - Automatic on Vercel + Supabase
  - No setup needed

Layer 2: Authentication
  - Supabase Auth (JWT tokens)
  - Access token: 1 hour expiry
  - Refresh token: 7 days
  - Admin 2FA: TOTP (Google Authenticator app)

Layer 3: Authorization
  - Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) on all tables
  - Next.js middleware protects /dashboard, /admin, /receptionist
  - Service role key (powerful) ONLY used in server-side API routes
  - NEVER use service role key in frontend/browser code

Layer 4: Input Validation
  - Zod schemas on all API routes
  - Phone format validation (BD format)
  - File type check server-side (not just extension)
  - Max file size: 10MB

Layer 5: Rate Limiting
  - 10 API requests per minute per IP
  - 5 failed login attempts → 15 min lockout
  - Configured in Vercel Edge middleware

Layer 6: File Security
  - Supabase Storage bucket: PRIVATE (not public)
  - Files served via signed URLs (expire 1 hour)
  - Allowed types: jpg, jpeg, png, pdf only

Layer 7: Admin Protection
  - 2FA mandatory for /admin
  - Admin session expires after 4 hours inactivity
  - Receptionist session expires after 8 hours
  - Role verified server-side on every admin API call

Layer 8: Environment Security
  - All API keys in .env.local
  - .env.local in .gitignore (NEVER committed to GitHub)
  - Server-only keys NEVER exposed to frontend
```

